Address: 2/8 Westmoreland Street St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
A rare find and room to move!!
Such a rare find is this 3 Bedroom Unit in a prime location ideal for downsizers, investors or first home buyers. "Space" is the key word here with ample room to move and built with the concept of open amenity rather than density. Investors reap a healthy return on this maintenance free property (approx $300 pw)
Located on a block of only 2, this amazing single level unit is tucked away at the rear, ensuring privacy and security. Close to all amenities in a sought after location, this property will impress the most discerning buyer.
The massive central lounge/dining area, complete with modern kitchen (s/s appliances and dishwasher), opens to a spacious side area large enough for entertaining family and friends.
3 Large bedrooms with BIR and central bathroom complete the ensemble for this perfectly positioned and planned home.
Single car parking, gas heating and s/s airconditioning ensure all the creature comforts are ticked off.
Located close to all the Geelong Region has to offer, this home is close to Geelong CBD, shopping and sporting complexes.

Description:
Exceptional Unit in Central Location
This beautiful unit will exceed your expectations at every turn. Offering spacious living, generous outdoor spaces and modern finishes, this property represents exceptional value and fantastic lifestyle.
Comprising 3 bedrooms, all with BIRs, master with ensuite, central bathroom, separate toilet and additional study or 4th bedroom. This unit is more than meets the eye.
With bedrooms situated at the front of the home, the central hallway leads you to a large open kitchen/dining/living room at the rear, a beautiful open space with ample windows and incoming light. The kitchen which includes stainless steel appliances, is well-equipped and situated overlooking the dining and living space.
Large sliding glass doors flawlessly connect the living to the outdoors with a large undercover merbau deck, a great entertaining space. And the outdoor area continues with a pretty garden area, with established trees for shade on the warmer days.
Every need has been catered for in this home, including gas heating, split system cooling, ceiling fans, solar-boosted continuous hot water and single remote garage with direct entry providing both convenience and security.
Situated only minutes from South Geelong Station, local shopping centres and sporting facilities, this court location offers a quiet area within close proximity to amenities as well as easy access to bus routes into Geelong and to the Surf Coast
If you're looking for low-maintenance, secure living without compromising on space, this is the unit for you. Approximate rental $360 - $380 per week.

Description:
Queen Anne Beauty in Leafy East Geelong
This beautiful family home exudes the warmth of a highly-prized architectural style in one of Geelong's most leafy and well-established inner-city locations. Beautifully positioned in prestigious Ryrie Street, close to the Waterfront, Botanic Gardens, CBD, prestigious schools and Garden Street cafe precinct, this ready-to-enjoy Queen Anne home has stylish, easy-flowing living areas, perfect for contemporary family life. Hidden behind high green hedges, a charming front garden and veranda with detailed timber fretwork has instant street appeal with refined style enhanced through preserved period features throughout the home including picture rails, skirting boards and detailed ceiling roses. Leading from an elegant hallway drenched in history are four generous bedrooms featuring soaring ceilings, polished Baltic pine floorboards, original fireplaces and built-in-robes. The master boats an ultra-modern ensuite drenched in light while a sparkling central bathroom showcases a ball and claw bath complemented by luxurious, modern fittings and fixtures. Head down the hallway to the rear of the home and the modern extension radiates an edgy but timeless energy. An impressive open-plan living and dining area overlooks a private, classically-designed backyard through French doors, and is complete with timber decking, landscaped gardens and feature brick paving. Overlooking the space is a masterfully-appointed kitchen that is flooded with an abundance of light and features modern stainless-steel appliances, stone benchtops and generous cupboard space. The indoor/outdoor transition is effortless with undercover decks and paved areas for entertaining throughout the year. Other highlights of this impressive home include a large study, central heating, double lock-up garage via rear lane, security system, large side driveway and another single lock-up garage for plenty of storage.

Description:
Sensational Victorian Masterpiece
Step inside this stunning Victorian style home and be wowed by the gorgeous, yet functional details of this residence. Sitting on a block size of 388m2 (approx.), in sought after East Geelong, this charming home has so much to offer and is ready for you to move in.
Head through the front door and find gorgeous timber floors throughout that accompany soft quality carpets. The centerpiece of this home is a dream come true for any entertainer, the fresh and sophisticated kitchen features gorgeous stone bench tops, 900mm freestanding Smeg gas cook top and oven, Asko white dishwasher, an abundance of storage with soft close features, under-mount sink and a walk-in pantry. The open plan living/dining area pleasantly features an open fire, split system, 3-metre-tall ceilings and tall glass stacker doors that open out to the deck. These stunning feature vaulted windows that provide streams of light to fill the living and dining area, a real special touch to this home.
A low maintenance backyard features a garden shed and side access into the carport. The heavenly finished backyard has plenty of luscious grass that is drenched in northerly sun; perfect for families, entertaining and pets.
The three spacious light-filled bedrooms welcomes you upon your entrance into the home, they all feature white shutters, high skirting boards and gorgeous 3.3-metre timber ceilings along with picture rails. The master suite enjoys a walk-in robe and luxury ensuite bathroom. Another bedroom features a fireplace and ceiling fan and the last enjoys a built-in robe, fireplace and ceiling fan. The spacious family bathroom is modernised with a stunning neutral palette featuring a double vanity and a shower over the bath. The laundry is very spacious which features an abundance of storage, bench space and room for all appliances.
This elegant home has been entirely renovated from top to bottom with the upmost love and passion to create a home forever. This home has been re-stumped as well as new plumbing, electrical and plastering throughout. Another special feature is an extension with the continuation of the original double gables, this home was refurbished to be lived in. The quality and appreciation of detail that has been poured into this home is something you don't see in most homes; this property is a real gem.
In the fabulous location of East Geelong this property is only a stone's throw away from South Geelong Train Station, Schools, the CBD and a short 500m walk to the Garden Street shops.

AN ARRAY OF POSSIBILITIES
Ideally located in East Geelong on an attractive north facing backyard allotment of 620m2 overlooking open space.
This home has endless possibilities, move straight in, with the potential to further enhance, extend, renovate, or demolish and develop, this really is a once in a lifetime opportunity.
Comprising of three bedrooms, master with built-in robe, separate lounge, updated bathroom, neat kitchen with dishwasher and sunroom to the rear that could be used as a study nook.

Close to schools, the Geelong CBD and Waterfront, this really is the perfect lifestyle opportunity.

Description:
Convenient & Secure Low Maintenance Townhouse
This immaculate 2BR townhouse presents a delightfully appealing opportunity for first home buyers, empty nesters, and investors alike! Offering a beautiful, open-plan interior with light-filled, neutral colours and expansive North facing windows that bring through the living areas an abundance of natural light, creating a warm and welcoming atmosphere throughout. Situated only minutes from the Geelong CBD and the picturesque Waterfront, South Geelong train station and the Bellarine Shopping Village, this immaculate town residence features 2 bedrooms with BIRs and a central bathroom with separate toilet. The spacious open plan living/dining leads to the fully equipped kitchen with modern appliances and ample cupboard/bench space. Other features include A/C and secure internal access to the automatic SLUG. Perfectly positioned in one of Geelong's up and coming suburbs is this fantastic opportunity sure to accommodate your every need.

Description:
The Ultimate Entertainer Inside and Out!
There is simply nothing more to do other than move in and make the most of what this beautifully appointed 4 bedroom home in the heart of Newcomb has to offer. Set on an impressive allotment of approximately 604 square metres the home is comprised of 4 spacious bedrooms, all with built in robes and ceiling fans, open plan living and dining room and separate kitchen/meals area that leads directly out to a stunning outdoor deck area that simply must be seen to be truly appreciated. Impressive additions include new carpet, ducted heating throughout, reverse cycle heating and cooling unit in lounge, fresh coat of paint inside and high quality fixtures and fittings in the bathroom and kitchen.
The timber ramp that leads into the wide hallway is a classy entry point to the home and the smart floor plan means that the large open plan living and dining area is the ideal place to entertain family and friends when it's too cold to utilize the amazing outside entertainment area with hand crafted open fire place while the backyard is large enough for the kids to play happily all year round.
There is ample car accommodation with a long, wide driveway leading down to a double car garage and workshop area; ideal for the home handyman, tradesman or green thumb while there is public transport located nearby that will take you the short 10 minute trip into the C.B.D. and with East Geelong shopping precinct, schools, health care facilities and 2 large shopping centres close by it really is the ideal central location for all types of buyers.
The Geelong market has seen extensive growth in the last 24 months and Newcomb is leading the way due to its incredibly close proximity to everything that Geelong and the Bellarine has to offer and the fantastic land component that comes with the meticulously presented homes being offered and this property is a prime example of that and with a projected rental return of app. $380 per week would be a perfect investment property for any shrewd investor. Get in first and prepare to be delighted!
